"KELLLOL Plan" to resolve the Ukrainian conflict: 

- termination of isolation of the Russian Federation: the establishment of diplomatic relations with Moscow and the termination of the "demonization" of Putin;

- peaceful negotiations: it is necessary to put pressure on Ukraine and Russia so that they agree on the ceasefire and begin negotiations;

- postpone the membership of Ukraine in NATO for 10 years. Allow Russia to preserve the restrained territories. Gradual abolition of sanctions and normalization of relations with the United States, provided that the peace agreements are concluded for Ukraine;

- Continuation of military assistance and bilateral security guarantees. Ukraine does not need to officially recognize the control of the Russian Federation, but it should refrain from changing the status quo by force;

- Potentially to stop US military assistance if Ukraine abandons peace negotiations.

